LAGOS – Kogi State, has sympathised with the government and people of Kwara State, the immediate families of the victims of the tragic boat accident that occurred at Egbu village in Patigi Local Government Area of the state on Tuesday. Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State on behalf of the government and people of Kogi, noted that the incident, involving over 100 citizens, is, to say the least, unfortunate. The condolence message read, “Our thoughts and prayers go out to the affected families, the community, and the entire state. “I commend the prompt response and rescue efforts of the Kwara State government, which have helped to minimise the number of casualties. To my esteemed brother, Governor Abdulrazaq Abdulrahman of Kwara State, I assure you of our unwavering support during this challenging period. “May the departed souls rest in peace, and may the affected families find solace and comfort during this difficult time, ”Bello stated.